                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/22941",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Great thanks for  your report!\nI also looked through the details in your post at ZFForum.\n\nThe bug is in some other place..\n\n{code}\nforeach ($this->_fields as $fNum => $fieldInfo) {\n    if ($fieldInfo->isIndexed) {\n        $this->_norms[$fNum] = $normfFile->readBytes($this->_docCount);\n    }\n}\n{code}\nIterates through all fields and this is correct. I've changed $fieldNum variable name to $fNum, to increase code readability and make everyone not confused with two differed meaning of input variable $fieldNum and iterating variable $fNum\n\nIf index segment uses single norms file, then all norms are stored within <segment_name>.nrm file instead of set of files (<segment_name>.f0, <segment_name>.f1, <segment_name>.f3, ...)\nAll norms are read at once at first request in this case.\n\nThat looks like <segment_name>.nrm file doesn't have enough data or Zend_Search_Lucene has some bug in some other place.\n\nCould you attach your index to the issue for test purposes?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-07-18T10:50:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-07-18T10:50:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23134",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jsloan",
                        "name": "jsloan",
                        "displayName": "jim sloan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The problem is still observed in 1.6RC1 so I have included the following for testing:\n+ \/IndexSource  (HTML source)\n+ \/collections  (Omnifind collection)\n+ \/library-1.6RC1 Search (Zend\/Search) \n+ \/Search_Omnifind_index.php (demo searches for 'test' and returns 1 hit; this matches the result set when the same search is run on Omnifind)\n\nI have patched \/library-1.6RC1\/Zend\/Search\/Lucene\/Index\/Segmentinfo.php so that the demo works with the Omnifind collection (line 951)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jsloan",
                        "name": "jsloan",
                        "displayName": "jim sloan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-07-28T06:57:34.000+0000",
